<!DOCTYPE html>
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
      xmlns:tal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/tal"
      xmlns:metal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/metal"
      xmlns:i18n="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/i18n"
      metal:use-macro="api.layout.macros['master']"
      i18n:domain="lasco">
<tal:block metal:fill-slot="content">

<h1 i18n:translate="">Help! I need somebody! Help!</h1>

<h2 i18n:translate="">Which access keys are available?</h2>

<p i18n:translate="help_access_keys_1">
   When viewing a single picture in an album, you may use access keys:
   <span class="key">p</span> to navigate to the previous
   picture, <span class="key">n</span> to navigate the next one.
</p>

<p i18n:translate="help_access_keys_2">
  How you invoke an access key depends on your browser
  (below <span class="key">?</span> has to be replaced by the access
  key you want to invoke):
</p>

<table class="listing">
  <tr class="odd">
    <td rowspan="2">Firefox</td>
    <td>
      <span class="key">Alt</span> + <span class="key">&#8679; Shift</span> + <span class="key">?</span>
      (Windows)
    </td>
  </tr>
  <tr class="odd">
    <td>
      <span class="key">Ctrl</span> + <span class="key">?</span> (Mac OS X)
    </td>
  </tr>
  <tr class="even">
    <td>Opera</td>
    <td>
      <span class="key">&#8679; Shift</span> + <span class="key">Esc</span> + <span class="key">?</span>
    </td>
  </tr>
  <tr class="odd">
    <td>Internet Explorer</td>
    <td><span class="key">Alt</span> + <span class="key">?</span></td>
  </tr>
  <tr class="even">
    <td rowspan="2">Chrome</td>
    <td><span class="key">Alt</span> + <span class="key">?</span> (Windows)</td>
  </tr>
  <tr class="even">
    <td>
      <span class="key">Ctrl</span> + <span class="key">&#8997; Option</span> + <span class="key">?</span>
      (Mac OS X)
    </td>
  </tr>
</table>

<h2 i18n:translate="">How do I change the language?</h2>

<p i18n:translate="help_language">
  You may change the language of the user interface by going to
  <a href="preferences">your preferences page</a>.
</p>

<h2 i18n:translate="">How to I change the colors?</h2>

<p i18n:translate="help_stylesheet">
  You may change the colors of the user interface by going to
  <a href="preferences'">your preferences page</a> and selecting a new
  color theme.
</p>

</tal:block>
</html>
